WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:42.280 --> 00:01:51.320
The Iron Mask

3
00:01:52.020 --> 00:01:55.590
Nice work out there, Ichiji, Niji.

4
00:02:00.100 --> 00:02:06.600
The war-torn Broc Coli is another victim of the fall 
of the Doflamingo regime, you could say.

5
00:02:07.520 --> 00:02:14.710
Their army could no longer acquire weapons
from Doflamingo, so they turned to us for help.

6
00:02:16.120 --> 00:02:19.450
They gave up on the idea of
merely suppressing their rivals...

7
00:02:19.450 --> 00:02:24.020
It's a good example of how halfhearted kindness
only leads to more bloodshed in the end.

8
00:02:24.450 --> 00:02:26.460
Who cares about the reason why?

9
00:02:26.460 --> 00:02:30.360
We just make it so whoever 
pays us gets to win, and that's it.

10
00:02:30.360 --> 00:02:34.530
If we had crushed both sides,
we could've earned even more money.

11
00:02:34.530 --> 00:02:37.500
That's what pirates would do.

12
00:02:37.510 --> 00:02:42.340
We're still a member nation
of the World Government.

13
00:02:42.930 --> 00:02:47.150
Speaking of which, Father,
the Reverie will take place soon.

14
00:02:47.150 --> 00:02:48.430
Yes.

15
00:02:49.130 --> 00:02:55.420
However, they'll likely strip us of our right
to attend the Reverie starting from this one.

16
00:02:55.420 --> 00:02:57.530
All of you, be prepared for it!

17
00:02:57.930 --> 00:03:01.100
The power that we'll get 
in exchange is tremendous!

18
00:03:01.910 --> 00:03:04.200
Germa will change!

19
00:03:07.210 --> 00:03:12.280
It's rare for anything to bring so much pleasure to Father.

20
00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:16.010
I can't believe you came in handy, after all.

21
00:03:16.890 --> 00:03:18.720
Sanji!

22
00:03:18.720 --> 00:03:22.080
We were surprised on the day that you disappeared.

23
00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:23.340
Truly.

24
00:03:24.890 --> 00:03:30.520
We used to talk about you from time to time.

25
00:03:30.860 --> 00:03:38.560
We wondered where the funniest place for you to die would be, and how it might happen.

26
00:03:43.410 --> 00:03:46.770
You still have food on your plate, Niji.
Eat all of it.

27
00:03:49.750 --> 00:03:53.380
This? I'll just leave it. 
I'm not hungry.

28
00:03:55.210 --> 00:04:01.470
I ate tons of chocolate earlier, 
and this sauce that's poured on it looks nasty.

29
00:04:01.470 --> 00:04:03.410
It's all sticky and gross.

30
00:04:04.140 --> 00:04:05.830
I'm throwing this away.

31
00:04:05.830 --> 00:04:07.000
Eat it!

32
00:04:08.690 --> 00:04:14.400
You don't know how valuable food is or how much work goes into cooking, you dumb prince!

33
00:04:14.770 --> 00:04:15.840
Dumb?!

34
00:04:16.490 --> 00:04:19.970
You're a weakling, Sanji!

35
00:04:19.970 --> 00:04:22.510
Don't you dare insult me,
much less give me orders!

36
00:04:22.960 --> 00:04:26.140
Call the head chef!
Where are you, Cosette?!

37
00:04:26.770 --> 00:04:31.020
Cosette
Head Chef

38
00:04:31.020 --> 00:04:36.250
Because you served this disgusting stuff,
my brother has offended me!

39
00:04:36.260 --> 00:04:39.120
Yes, sir! I'm sorry!

40
00:04:39.430 --> 00:04:42.330
I shouldn't serve anything
unpalatable to you...

41
00:04:42.330 --> 00:04:43.200
Okay.

42
00:04:47.100 --> 00:04:49.190
Stay right there, Cosette.

43
00:05:25.840 --> 00:05:30.050
You bastard...
How low will you sink?!

44
00:05:30.050 --> 00:05:33.410
Are you trying
to leave a scar on a lady's face?!

45
00:05:59.160 --> 00:06:03.210
What did you say? A lady?

46
00:06:03.990 --> 00:06:07.050
Why are you defending a mere kitchen maid?!

47
00:06:13.390 --> 00:06:15.390
What a gentleman.

48
00:06:16.380 --> 00:06:18.420
Now the food's on the floor.

49
00:06:19.510 --> 00:06:24.100
This is aligot.
It's a mixture of potatoes and cheese.

50
00:06:25.130 --> 00:06:27.600
Your Highness, I'll clean it!

51
00:06:28.770 --> 00:06:33.800
Potatoes strengthen the immune system
and stabilize blood pressure.

52
00:06:34.230 --> 00:06:37.030
They're very nutritious.

53
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:37.030
Huh...?

54
00:06:37.030 --> 00:06:39.380
And maybe because you guys are so special,

55
00:06:39.700 --> 00:06:42.710
the cut of meat in the confit
has been carefully selected too.

56
00:06:44.250 --> 00:06:47.210
It's a very elaborate dish
to make for breakfast.

57
00:06:49.720 --> 00:06:51.950
Oh, please don't, Your Highness!

58
00:06:51.950 --> 00:06:54.030
Royalty mustn't eat food off the floor!

59
00:06:55.460 --> 00:06:58.920
Hey, are you out of your mind?!
That's disgusting!

60
00:06:59.260 --> 00:07:01.530
It's perfectly flavored, too.

61
00:07:04.300 --> 00:07:06.840
The spirit of the poor has taken root in you!

62
00:07:08.410 --> 00:07:11.140
Stop doing such a disgraceful thing!

63
00:07:11.270 --> 00:07:14.010
Don't, Niji! He hasn't been married yet!

64
00:07:27.830 --> 00:07:29.690
Thank you, sir.

65
00:07:29.690 --> 00:07:32.200
You only bring shame to the Vinsmokes.

66
00:07:32.580 --> 00:07:37.740
What's shameful to me is
being part of this family!

67
00:07:37.740 --> 00:07:38.860
What?!

68
00:07:39.260 --> 00:07:45.210
An idiot who has no respect for food.
A man who beats a woman!

69
00:07:45.210 --> 00:07:50.110
The arrogance of royalty that compels you
to see your servants as less than human!

70
00:07:50.480 --> 00:07:54.490
Everything about you guys 
goes against what I stand for!

71
00:07:54.490 --> 00:07:59.220
What you're saying is the kind of
nonsense all those losers spout, Sanji.

72
00:08:00.430 --> 00:08:04.230
I've never understood the way you see things.

73
00:08:05.950 --> 00:08:09.100
Royalty operates by its own set of rules!

74
00:08:09.100 --> 00:08:11.470
You're the unreasonable one!

75
00:08:14.140 --> 00:08:18.800
He's right.
You're more wrong than ever.

76
00:08:20.480 --> 00:08:25.640
Is it because of the bad influence 
from this man, Sanji?

77
00:08:34.490 --> 00:08:38.530
Big Mom's ability to collect information
is greater than people think.

78
00:08:38.530 --> 00:08:42.890
So you were working at his
restaurant until two years ago.

79
00:08:42.890 --> 00:08:45.200
We've already zeroed in on its location, too.

80
00:08:45.660 --> 00:08:49.280
Seems like this picture was taken recently.

81
00:08:49.280 --> 00:08:52.840
The sea restaurant, Baratie !

82
00:08:56.920 --> 00:09:00.990
What's wrong? You're turning pale.

83
00:09:02.090 --> 00:09:05.220
Where did your spirit from earlier go, Sanji?

84
00:09:05.880 --> 00:09:09.760
Say something. Huh? Hey!

85
00:09:22.440 --> 00:09:23.920
What are those?

86
00:09:23.920 --> 00:09:26.980
These are bracelets 
to prevent him from escaping-bon.

87
00:09:28.550 --> 00:09:31.990
Seems like both the Straw
Hats and Sanji himself are

88
00:09:31.990 --> 00:09:35.360
going to oppose this marriage-bon.

89
00:09:35.360 --> 00:09:41.630
I'll lend you these bracelets
and tell you his weak point just in case-soir.

90
00:09:42.600 --> 00:09:44.430
His weak point?

91
00:09:47.940 --> 00:09:53.400
Well, only in the worst-case scenario
where you refuse to comply

92
00:09:53.400 --> 00:09:59.030
will I stoop to asking you if you want us to chop his head off.

93
00:10:05.420 --> 00:10:11.460
Don't do anything stupid.
You know what we're capable of.

94
00:10:11.460 --> 00:10:13.410
Don't ever resist.

95
00:10:13.410 --> 00:10:17.660
Give up on your friends
and accept your marriage to Pudding.

96
00:10:18.130 --> 00:10:21.990
Then, everything will wrap up neatly.

97
00:10:36.610 --> 00:10:39.650
What happened to your leg?

98
00:10:40.070 --> 00:10:41.750
Why?!

99
00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:46.620
I can't think of any reason for you to be kind to me!

100
00:10:46.620 --> 00:10:49.730
Why...? Why did you?!

101
00:10:51.820 --> 00:10:57.570
Because you...
have the same dream as me.

102
00:10:58.980 --> 00:11:01.010
The All Blue...

103
00:11:06.760 --> 00:11:10.960
This is awesome, you damn geezer!
Is this the sea restaurant?

104
00:11:10.960 --> 00:11:13.280
We're gonna be busy!

105
00:11:13.280 --> 00:11:15.120
We'll be fine 'cause I'm here!

106
00:11:18.990 --> 00:11:20.320
Hey, little eggplant!

107
00:11:23.830 --> 00:11:25.790
You're too slow, little eggplant!

108
00:11:25.790 --> 00:11:27.500
I'm not, you damn geezer!

109
00:11:28.500 --> 00:11:31.170
Fooling around with a woman again,
little eggplant!

110
00:11:31.170 --> 00:11:32.240
Little eggplant!

111
00:11:32.590 --> 00:11:33.500
Little eggplant!

112
00:11:33.710 --> 00:11:34.810
Little eggplant!

113
00:11:35.130 --> 00:11:36.010
Little eggplant!

114
00:11:36.400 --> 00:11:37.380
Little eggplant!

115
00:11:37.780 --> 00:11:39.990
Little eggplant!

116
00:11:45.930 --> 00:11:46.980
Sanji!

117
00:11:48.980 --> 00:11:52.190
Don't catch a cold.

118
00:12:03.700 --> 00:12:06.770
Owner Zeff!!

119
00:12:08.540 --> 00:12:13.630
Thank you for all the damn things 
you've done for me over all these years!

120
00:12:13.630 --> 00:12:18.380
I'll never forget your kindness...
for the rest of my life!

121
00:12:31.230 --> 00:12:34.930
Let's have a peaceful wedding tomorrow.

122
00:12:35.320 --> 00:12:40.590
We'll have lunch 
with Big Mom and Pudding today.

123
00:12:40.590 --> 00:12:42.710
Prepare to leave for her castle.

124
00:12:43.030 --> 00:12:45.530
Okay, Sanji?

125
00:12:50.540 --> 00:12:53.150
Damn Straw Hat... Where did he go?

126
00:12:54.670 --> 00:12:56.050
Search for him.

127
00:12:58.180 --> 00:13:01.520
Ten minutes... is long...

128
00:13:02.260 --> 00:13:04.960
I can't even use haki.

129
00:13:12.200 --> 00:13:14.110
Is somebody there?

130
00:13:22.880 --> 00:13:25.630
Somebody, help! Call a doctor!

131
00:13:26.760 --> 00:13:28.880
Hey, stay with me!

132
00:13:28.880 --> 00:13:32.610
Damn! They waited until I wasn't around!

133
00:13:33.030 --> 00:13:35.660
What did she do to deserve this?!

134
00:13:40.350 --> 00:13:43.500
They beat a woman unconscious...

135
00:13:45.900 --> 00:13:50.470
I've never met such scum!

136
00:13:50.470 --> 00:13:53.240
It's your fault, Sanji.

137
00:13:53.240 --> 00:13:54.470
Yonji!

138
00:13:56.740 --> 00:13:59.890
You gave a woman of low birth
a taste of self-confidence.

139
00:14:01.150 --> 00:14:03.420
What do you mean by that, you bastard?!

140
00:14:05.920 --> 00:14:10.700
Do you want to see Niji?
Obviously, he's the one who did it.

141
00:14:11.660 --> 00:14:14.270
Follow me. I'll take you to him.

142
00:14:21.560 --> 00:14:24.670
You're gonna be fine. Don't worry.

143
00:14:26.230 --> 00:14:28.610
What's wrong? Are you coming?

144
00:14:31.400 --> 00:14:35.090
Yeah, I'm more than happy to!

145
00:14:44.060 --> 00:14:45.000
This is...

146
00:14:46.240 --> 00:14:48.060
You were curious, weren't you?

147
00:14:48.060 --> 00:14:51.500
We were never allowed in here as kids.

148
00:15:27.920 --> 00:15:32.130
54 Type MBs. 30 Type MSTs.

149
00:15:32.130 --> 00:15:35.210
And 21 Type MHs need to be restocked.

150
00:15:35.210 --> 00:15:36.410
Got it.

151
00:15:58.950 --> 00:16:01.800
What are they?!

152
00:16:06.790 --> 00:16:09.250
Do you want to know what they are?

153
00:16:09.670 --> 00:16:13.920
Germa 66 is feared around the world.

154
00:16:13.920 --> 00:16:16.440
And these are its soldiers!

155
00:16:36.500 --> 00:16:38.550
Minister Cracker!

156
00:16:38.550 --> 00:16:40.950
Cracker?! Is that him?!

157
00:16:50.190 --> 00:16:52.760
What's wrong, Kingbaum?

158
00:16:52.760 --> 00:16:56.090
Why are you taking Straw Hat's side?

159
00:16:58.570 --> 00:17:01.050
There is a good reason for it...

160
00:17:13.210 --> 00:17:15.670
No excuse.

161
00:17:16.170 --> 00:17:18.450
I'm gonna kill you all!

162
00:17:28.390 --> 00:17:29.930
What's with him?

163
00:17:30.560 --> 00:17:34.680
Woman, I'm Sweet Commander Cracker.

164
00:17:35.750 --> 00:17:37.860
Don't touch...

165
00:17:45.910 --> 00:17:47.710
my friend!

166
00:17:48.550 --> 00:17:50.550
Straw Hat!

167
00:17:58.290 --> 00:18:02.400
The soldiers of Germa 66?!

168
00:18:04.400 --> 00:18:06.430
Why are they in water?

169
00:18:06.430 --> 00:18:08.330
It's a bio-culture liquid.

170
00:18:08.760 --> 00:18:12.770
They all have the same face...
Are they actually alive?

171
00:18:12.770 --> 00:18:15.560
Sanji, human beings...

172
00:18:16.050 --> 00:18:17.640
can be built!

173
00:18:18.730 --> 00:18:22.230
Germa has been a kingdom of science
for generations.

174
00:18:22.230 --> 00:18:26.050
Believe it or not, our father is a brilliant scientist.

175
00:18:26.940 --> 00:18:29.880
Before we were born,

176
00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:33.410
he was part of a lawless research team
in a foreign territory

177
00:18:33.410 --> 00:18:38.350
where he was studying and developing weapons with the great Dr. Vegapunk.

178
00:18:38.350 --> 00:18:40.330
He was with Vegapunk?!

179
00:18:40.710 --> 00:18:42.520
Yes, when he was younger.

180
00:18:44.040 --> 00:18:47.630
What Vegapunk discovered 
at that time was the presence of

181
00:18:47.630 --> 00:18:50.720
hereditary elements within living things!

182
00:18:50.720 --> 00:18:54.430
It was just one step away from
usurping God's place.

183
00:18:54.430 --> 00:18:58.580
In essence, he found the blueprints of life.

184
00:18:59.920 --> 00:19:05.020
The World Government saw it as dangerous
and arrested Vegapunk.

185
00:19:05.020 --> 00:19:10.530
The research team was disbanded.
Or rather, it was absorbed by the government.

186
00:19:10.530 --> 00:19:14.630
However, our father escaped
the government's reach

187
00:19:14.630 --> 00:19:18.080
and continued his research here in Germa.

188
00:19:18.600 --> 00:19:23.270
The research into replicating and augmenting life itself.

189
00:19:24.640 --> 00:19:28.630
Thus leading to the birth of this secret facility!

190
00:19:28.630 --> 00:19:34.180
They're all clones of
just a few talented soldiers!

191
00:19:34.180 --> 00:19:36.390
They're clone soldiers!

192
00:19:36.390 --> 00:19:38.020
Clone?!

193
00:19:45.200 --> 00:19:49.260
Of course, none of them are aware of that.

194
00:19:49.800 --> 00:19:51.320
You see, Sanji?

195
00:19:52.220 --> 00:19:59.210
Many countries are afraid of our army,
but at the same time, they wish to have it.

196
00:19:59.440 --> 00:20:02.580
It only makes sense; 
they are mighty and subservient.

197
00:20:03.150 --> 00:20:08.040
They're programmed not to fear death
and not to turn on their masters.

198
00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:11.740
When they die, we can just replace them.

199
00:20:11.740 --> 00:20:15.460
It takes five years to create
a 20-year-old soldier.

200
00:20:16.010 --> 00:20:19.290
This is the depot where we
keep a stock of the soldiers.

201
00:20:21.500 --> 00:20:25.280
Look. It only takes 
five years to create them,

202
00:20:27.340 --> 00:20:30.740
but they look like they've been around
for two decades.

203
00:20:30.740 --> 00:20:33.010
Stop it! That's enough!

204
00:20:34.830 --> 00:20:36.910
I'm going to be sick.

205
00:20:48.670 --> 00:20:49.990
Sanji.

206
00:20:54.390 --> 00:20:57.840
When we heard that you became a pirate,

207
00:20:57.840 --> 00:21:02.240
I thought maybe our little failure was actually growing up a bit.

208
00:21:04.270 --> 00:21:06.910
But you ended up just as disappointing as ever.

209
00:21:07.480 --> 00:21:08.810
Niji!

210
00:21:10.320 --> 00:21:11.650
You sick bastard...

211
00:21:20.760 --> 00:21:23.540
What are you doing over there?

212
00:21:25.460 --> 00:21:27.280
You kitchen maid.

213
00:21:32.810 --> 00:21:34.090
Um...

214
00:21:39.600 --> 00:21:41.220
What did Cosette-chan do...

215
00:21:43.320 --> 00:21:45.810
to deserve that?!

216
00:21:48.620 --> 00:21:52.660
What you did was a high crime!
I'll teach you a lesson!

217
00:21:53.560 --> 00:21:59.400
Wait, Sanji! Don't forget that we're
holding a hostage in the East Blue!

218
00:22:01.840 --> 00:22:03.220
Stealth.

219
00:22:04.470 --> 00:22:09.500
I can't believe it...
Have you taken a liking to that kitchen maid?

220
00:22:10.310 --> 00:22:15.270
Don't fight back.
Otherwise, there will be blood in the East Blue.

221
00:22:16.650 --> 00:22:17.750
Henry...

222
00:22:18.820 --> 00:22:20.020
Needle!

223
00:22:46.110 --> 00:22:48.110
You should've told me.

224
00:22:48.910 --> 00:22:52.480
If I knew you were in love
with that kitchen maid,

225
00:22:52.480 --> 00:22:55.650
I wouldn't have messed up her face.

226
00:22:55.980 --> 00:23:01.250
But if you have no problem
with that swollen face,

227
00:23:01.250 --> 00:23:04.340
I'll appoint her to be
your servant right away.

228
00:23:06.360 --> 00:23:09.550
Once again, welcome back, Sanji.

229
00:23:10.520 --> 00:23:13.100
To the Vinsmoke family!

230
00:23:16.370 --> 00:23:21.880
I think it's high time 
we reestablish the hierarchy here.

231
00:23:25.450 --> 00:23:29.320
You are... a failure.

232
00:23:40.380 --> 00:23:45.090
Listen! You children are my 
greatest scientific achievements!

233
00:23:45.090 --> 00:23:48.910
You were born as superhumans
through scientific modifications

234
00:23:48.910 --> 00:23:52.680
representing the best that
research has to offer!

235
00:23:53.100 --> 00:23:56.450
Without living under the
sway of foolish emotions,

236
00:23:56.450 --> 00:23:59.900
each of you will eventually
lead your own troops

237
00:23:59.900 --> 00:24:07.530
and one day rule Germa 66 with the ever-evolving power of science!

238
00:24:07.910 --> 00:24:11.300
I have given you the ability. 
The rest comes down to discipline!

239
00:24:11.300 --> 00:24:13.600
Yes, Father!

240
00:24:36.350 --> 00:24:38.390
Now, Prince Sanji!

241
00:25:00.250 --> 00:25:02.330
Ow, ow, ow...

242
00:25:21.310 --> 00:25:23.270
Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

243
00:25:41.880 --> 00:25:43.550
Where's Sanji?

244
00:25:44.050 --> 00:25:45.060
I don't know.

245
00:25:59.430 --> 00:26:01.180
Come on. Come on.

246
00:26:01.180 --> 00:26:02.910
Come here.

247
00:26:08.650 --> 00:26:11.010
Stop playing with a turtle!

248
00:26:11.010 --> 00:26:13.030
How dare you!

249
00:26:13.740 --> 00:26:15.610
Don't talk to me like that!

250
00:26:18.110 --> 00:26:20.280
Humph! That'll teach ya!

251
00:26:20.660 --> 00:26:23.360
– Prince Sanji!
– Prince Niji!

252
00:26:39.520 --> 00:26:41.110
Stop! Ouch!

253
00:26:43.110 --> 00:26:45.820
I give up! Niji!

254
00:26:47.650 --> 00:26:49.990
Oh, please stop!

255
00:26:57.040 --> 00:26:58.580
Your Highness...

256
00:26:58.580 --> 00:27:00.960
Let go! I still wanna hit him!

257
00:27:03.540 --> 00:27:08.640
Why is Sanji weaker than the others?
He's lagging far behind the others' scores.

258
00:27:12.600 --> 00:27:15.140
We have the test results.

259
00:27:15.140 --> 00:27:20.520
The Young Masters Ichiji, Niji, and Yonji 
are making excellent progress.

260
00:27:20.520 --> 00:27:22.690
Their exoskeletons are developing well,

261
00:27:22.690 --> 00:27:28.490
and their resilience and strength 
are equivalent to full-grown men.

262
00:27:29.100 --> 00:27:33.600
However, Prince Sanji is...
It pains me to say...

263
00:27:37.500 --> 00:27:39.750
What is it? Say it.

264
00:27:40.610 --> 00:27:44.210
He must be considered a failure.

265
00:27:45.630 --> 00:27:51.050
We thought we successfully manipulated
the hereditary elements for all four of them.

266
00:27:51.050 --> 00:27:57.160
But for some reason, Sanji's hereditary elements
are no different from when he was born.

267
00:27:58.200 --> 00:27:59.420
So you mean...

268
00:28:00.430 --> 00:28:04.630
Prince Sanji is nothing but a human.

269
00:28:12.360 --> 00:28:14.990
Why do you help me?

270
00:28:14.990 --> 00:28:17.540
You don't want me to?

271
00:28:17.540 --> 00:28:19.410
I do!

272
00:28:19.410 --> 00:28:21.790
Reiju, you're so kind.

273
00:28:21.790 --> 00:28:23.650
Shut up! Be quiet!

274
00:28:25.630 --> 00:28:29.130
You're kind, but why do you laugh at me?

275
00:28:29.130 --> 00:28:34.140
What else can I do?!
If I try to stop them, they'll bully me too.

276
00:28:34.140 --> 00:28:35.490
I don't want that!

277
00:28:38.430 --> 00:28:42.830
Book Title: "Noland the Liar"
Devil Fruits

278
00:28:41.600 --> 00:28:42.830
Oh, there he is!

279
00:28:44.730 --> 00:28:46.180
You can eat that.

280
00:28:47.270 --> 00:28:49.410
I made it for you.

281
00:28:52.900 --> 00:28:54.320
Is it good?

282
00:28:55.600 --> 00:28:59.290
Sanji! Are you cooking food for rats again?!

283
00:28:59.290 --> 00:29:02.870
Royalty mustn't serve anyone!
How many times do I have to tell you this?!

284
00:29:02.870 --> 00:29:04.320
But, I...

285
00:29:05.420 --> 00:29:09.790
Your mother is dead!
Stop chasing her shadow!

286
00:29:10.800 --> 00:29:14.700
Unlike your siblings, you have no talent!

287
00:29:14.700 --> 00:29:19.100
Therefore, you must work 10 times harder...
no, 100 times harder than the others!

288
00:29:19.100 --> 00:29:24.710
You are a piece of my plan 
to restore Germa to glory!

289
00:29:24.710 --> 00:29:26.510
Do not let me down!

290
00:29:33.450 --> 00:29:36.320
Never cook again!

291
00:29:52.590 --> 00:29:56.050
Is that how you run, Sanji?!

292
00:29:58.190 --> 00:29:59.600
No progress.

293
00:29:59.600 --> 00:30:02.540
– So he has no potential.
– Right.

294
00:30:03.140 --> 00:30:06.420
What a waste of life.

295
00:30:06.420 --> 00:30:08.440
What should we do?

296
00:30:10.690 --> 00:30:14.400
An unthinkable shipwreck... I mourn!

297
00:30:14.400 --> 00:30:19.530
I was expecting all five of them
to lead Germa into the future together!

298
00:30:19.530 --> 00:30:24.600
I have lost a promising son!

299
00:30:28.250 --> 00:30:30.350
What?! What is this?!

300
00:30:32.050 --> 00:30:37.150
What's this? I can't take it off!
What are you guys doing?!

301
00:30:37.900 --> 00:30:40.140
Did Sanji really die?

302
00:30:40.140 --> 00:30:43.120
I don't know. 
Who really cares about him anyway?

303
00:30:51.860 --> 00:30:55.030
Wait! I don't wanna be in here!

304
00:30:55.030 --> 00:30:56.560
Let me out!

305
00:30:56.560 --> 00:30:59.950
Don't leave me behind!
I'm scared! I'm gonna die!

306
00:31:00.280 --> 00:31:01.740
I want my dad!

307
00:31:01.740 --> 00:31:04.810
Dad! Help! They're gonna kill me!

308
00:31:06.620 --> 00:31:10.080
This was His Majesty's decision.

309
00:31:10.080 --> 00:31:12.380
What? Dad's decision?

310
00:31:12.380 --> 00:31:15.150
No way! There must be a mistake!

311
00:31:15.510 --> 00:31:22.590
His Majesty said that he wants 
to pretend that you were never born.

312
00:31:22.990 --> 00:31:23.830
What?

313
00:31:41.110 --> 00:31:42.990
Why...?

314
00:31:44.030 --> 00:31:47.660
Please let me out, Dad...

315
00:31:47.660 --> 00:31:52.170
I'm sorry... 
I'm sorry that I was born weak!

316
00:31:52.170 --> 00:31:56.560
Help me... Dad, help me!

317
00:31:56.560 --> 00:31:59.880
Dad!
